law.text:
// EFFECTIVE UNTIL SEPTEMBER 30, 2013 PER CHAPTER 426 OF 2012 //
The Commission may study and make a finding as to whether a group is socially or economically disadvantaged as a result of discrimination in the public or private sector that affects the group's utilization and participation in contracting or procurement with the Commission.
If the Commission finds that a program is necessary to remedy discrimination against a minority, the Commission shall establish a Minority Business Enterprise Utilization Program to facilitate participation of responsible certified minority business enterprises in contracts awarded by the Commission for goods, services, and construction.
